This sample shows how to call GetStatusAsync and parse the result.

Uri endpoint = new Uri("<https://my-service.azure.com>");
AzureKeyCredential credential = new AzureKeyCredential("<key>");
FaceAsync client = new FaceClient(endpoint, credential).GetFaceAsyncClient();

Response response = await client.GetStatusAsync("<operationId>", null);

JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(response.ContentStream).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("status").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("createdDateTime").ToString());

This sample shows how to call GetStatusAsync with all parameters and parse the result.

